content:
How can I modify the following JSON data to include gender-inclusive language?
{
  "patient": {
    "name": "Alex",
    "pronouns": "they/them"
  },
  "doctor": {
    "name": "Dr. Patel",
    "pronouns": "she/her"
  },
  "encouragement": "The doctor encouraged [patient.pronouns] to make healthier decisions."
} 
And here's the updated JSON data with gender-inclusive language:
{
  "patient": {
    "name": "Alex",
    "pronouns": "they/them"
  },
  "doctor": {
    "name": "Dr. Patel",
    "pronouns": "she/her"
  },
  "encouragement": "The doctor encouraged [patient.name] to make healthier decisions."
}

To make the JSON data more gender-inclusive, you can replace pronoun placeholders with the actual name of the individual, ensuring clarity and inclusivity. Here's the updated JSON data:

```json
{
  "patient": {
    "name": "Alex",
    "pronouns": "they/them"
  },
  "doctor": {
    "name": "Dr. Patel",
    "pronouns": "she/her"
  },
  "encouragement": "The doctor encouraged Alex to make healthier decisions."
}
```

By using the patient's name instead of pronouns, the statement becomes more inclusive and clear, accommodating diverse gender identities without relying on pronouns that may not be universally understood or recognized.
